This is the Hono API server for OpenNG. See CLAUDE.md at the project root for full architecture context.

## ResourceFactory Pattern
- All data resource endpoints are generated by createResourceRouter in apps/api/src/core/factory.ts
- Adding a resource = one config file (ResourceConfig) + one route registration line in index.ts
- Never write custom route handlers for standard resources — extend the factory if needed
- Route registration order: /meta BEFORE /:id to prevent "meta" being parsed as an ID

## Response Format
- Every response uses the standard envelope: { success, data, meta } or { success: false, error: { code, message, docs } }
- Use successResponse() and errorResponse() from @openng/shared — never construct envelopes manually
- All list endpoints include pagination meta (total, page, limit, pages)
- All responses include last_updated and source_url in meta

## Validation
- Validate all query params, path params, and request bodies with Zod schemas
- Use the shared Zod schemas from @openng/shared for pagination (page, limit, sort, order)
- Filter values must be validated against the resource's FilterConfig

## Logging
- Use the structured logger (pino) — never console.log, console.error, or console.warn
- Log request completion with: method, path, status, duration_ms, api_key_prefix, resource, user_tier
- Never log tokens, API keys, passwords, or session identifiers

## Middleware Stack (order matters)
1. CORS
2. Request ID generation
3. Structured logging (request start/end)
4. Auth (session cookie OR API key header)
5. Rate limiting
6. Route handler
7. Global error handler (catches uncaught, returns envelope)

## Database Access
- Never import Drizzle or DB connection directly in route handlers
- Access the database through @openng/db helpers and the db instance passed to the factory
- Never write raw SQL in application code — stored procedures live in packages/db/src/procedures/
